This paper deals with the performance analysis of mobile multicell networks, which is a topic related to network infrastructure and communication systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves modeling and analysis of queueing networks, which falls under the category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper discusses joint probability distributions, which is a topic related to information theory and falls under the category of cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also uses a decomposition-composition approach, which is a technique used in mathematical optimization and falls under the category of cs.PF (Performance). Finally, the paper validates its results through experiments, which involves data analysis and falls under the category of cs.MA (Machine Learning).
